<br>
I mean that on DG, everyone is so rampently pro-Druid that they beat each other down trying to come up with the best new demand to place on VI.  They create wild petitions which drastically underestimate the real usefulness of their class, and use it as a demand for sweeping changes.  Anyone who disagrees is labled anti-Druid and quickly chastised.  The same thing is happening here.<br>
<br>
You guys wanted indifferent pets, you got it<br>
You wanted help for pets against AoEs, you got it<br>
You wanted pets to do more damage, you got it<br>
You wanted the haste cap lifted, you got it<br>
You wanted an improvement in nuking, you got it (Ancient retuned, best improvement of nukes for any class in original PoP spell line-up)<br>
You wanted pet XP penalty removed, you got it (thanks to Aaldawen for pointing out my major ommision)<br>
<br>
Was this good enough?  Noooooooooo!  Druids got very <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    minor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> improvements in their nukes for PoP, but Magi were soooooooo jealous that Druids could nuke for a few more points of damage, max.  Magi demanded even <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    better</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> spells!  Now you get what can only be described as a fantastically overpowered spell for it's level.  A few people try to rationally point out why it is overpowered, but they are immediately shot down!<br>
<br>
&quot;you're anti-Mage!&quot;<br>
&quot;don't get us Nerfed!&quot;<br>
&quot;this is good for us, don't get it changed!&quot;<br>
etc...<br>
<br>
I submit to you that the vast majority of you would never call <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    any</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> improvement to Magi overpowered.  You're so selfish and self-centered that you just want VI to gimmie gimmie gimmie gimmie  gimmie gimmie gimmie.<br>
<br>
A few people tried to point out the hypocricy of crying &quot;Nerf!&quot; when Druids got slightly better nukes, and Necros actually got a decent (but no where <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    near</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> effecient) nuke, then immediately turn around and defend a nuke which is better than anything Wizards get before lvl 64.  Those people where immediately ridiculed and called names, not based on any facts, but just based on the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    feeling</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that most of you have that Magi should get <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    more.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
How far is too far?  What if you get Lures?  What if you get Root?  What if you get Summon: TL to &lt;every Wizard location&gt;, what if you get Deity-Bane spells?  What if you get SoW, Snare, Heals, Slows, etc?  Where are you ever going to draw the line?  I don't think most of you would ever draw the line.  Any new spell/ability added on the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Test</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> server will instantly be latched onto with a loud, unanimous cry of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    MINE!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Any indication that said new spell/skill <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    might</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> not go &quot;Live&quot; well be regarded as a &quot;Nerf,&quot; and vicious VI bashing will commence.<br>
<br>
Get a grip.  This board used to be constructive, a place where people parsed logs, pointed out real problems, made reasonable suggestions, etc.  Now it's a playground for wild fantasies and mile-long Christmas lists of demnds.<br>
<br>
You need to realize that there is more than one class in this game.  Any improvements made to one class need to be weighed very carefully with respect to other class' abilities.  It's not productive to demand any change which will improve the power of your class, just for the sake of making your class powerful.  If you end up being overpowered, you will just end up getting Nerfed down the road, and there will be much wailing and gnashing of teeth.  Yes we all want Uber blast of Pwning, but the fact of the matter is that spell should probably not be given to most classes in the game.<br>
