I've gone over the LoS issue, frankly to me it's being blown way out of proportion.  Yes it can be tricky, but in no way does it negate the spell.  If anything you just have to pay a little more attention instead of mashing your /cast # hotkey.<br>
<br>
The simple fact is, FoT had a better ratio than GSS, had better DPS, it cast faster, and it only did 100 less max damage.  Being a bolt does not negate all those factors.  It wasn't until lvl 64 that Wizards got a spell which matched the DPS and casting time of FoT, and even then it had much lower ratio and did exactly the same max damage.  Finally at 65 there was a Wizard spell with better DPS, but a much worse ratio.  The only non-Ancient Wizard spell to match ratio was ISoS, which has abysmal DPS.<br>
<br>
Now, Magi (myself included) like to complain a lot when Druids step on their nuking toes.  The above situation is almost identical to Moonfire vs. every Mage nuke, yet some how Magi were all for FoT.  That is blatantly hypocritical and that's what I was trying to point out.<br>
<br>
I've always said Magi should get a bigger nuke at 60.  I proposed a 1.4k bolt months ago in my orignal post on lvl 60 nukes.  Since the PoP spells have been filtering in, I removed all my pre-PoP suggestions since they no longer have much baring.  The fact is I still support a large bolt in the early 60s, somewhere in the 1.4-1.6k range.  A ratio of 3.75 (like FoT was originally) seems quite fitting.  I don't have a problem with Magi getting a 2k nuke at 65, either, as long as due care is given not to come close to Wizards with ratio or DPS.<br>
<br>
You must remember, Wizards nuke <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  only.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  That is the only form of damage they bring to the table, and they have to be far and away better than any other class at nuking.  Classes like Druids who bring a lot of utility, Magi who have pets (really just super-effecient DoTs) and small utility, Enchanters with buffs and CC, etc all have other things they do well besides nuking.  All those classes have much more to bring to the table than nukes.  It's just not balanced for Magi, Druids, Enchanters, or any class to get nukes which are nearly as good, or situationally better than Wizards, when all those classes can either do massive damage through other means, or provide highly valuable functions to assist a group/raid in other ways. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uusrbinperldashw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>usrbinperl dashw</A> at: 10/19/02 7:40:11 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ushanre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shanre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#333333>(10/19/02 9:23:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=363.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Heh</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
